<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="627" type="discussion">
Specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="J. A. Allen" authorityYear="1906" box="[967,1126,3002,3035]" class="Mammalia" family="Molossidae" genus="Molossus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="627" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sinaloae">M. sinaloae</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingRegion box="[1228,1338,3002,3035]" country="Mexico" name="Yucatan" pageId="8" pageNumber="627">Yucatan</collectingRegion>
were described as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gonzalez-Ruiz, Ramirez-Pulido &amp; Arroyo-Cabrales" authorityYear="2011" box="[998,1140,3042,3075]" class="Mammalia" family="Molossidae" genus="Molossus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="627" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="alvarezi">M. alvarezi</taxonomicName>
based on morphology. Based on genetic data, individuals of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="J. A. Allen" authorityYear="1906" box="[836,987,3120,3153]" class="Mammalia" family="Molossidae" genus="Molossus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="627" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sinaloae">M. sinaloae</taxonomicName>
from Central and South America cluster with M. alvarexi and not with individuals from Pacific slope of 
<collectingCountry name="Mexico" pageId="8" pageNumber="627">Mexico</collectingCountry>
where the type locality of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="J. A. Allen" authorityYear="1906" box="[1163,1313,3239,3272]" class="Mammalia" family="Molossidae" genus="Molossus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="627" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sinaloae">M. sinaloae</taxonomicName>
is located. Therefore, distribution of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gonzalez-Ruiz, Ramirez-Pulido &amp; Arroyo-Cabrales" authorityYear="2011" class="Mammalia" family="Molossidae" genus="Molossus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="627" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="alvarezi">M. alvarezi</taxonomicName>
was expanded to South America, and distribution of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="J. A. Allen" authorityYear="1906" box="[347,496,3358,3391]" class="Mammalia" family="Molossidae" genus="Molossus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="627" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sinaloae">M. sinaloae</taxonomicName>
was restricted to western part of 
<collectingCountry box="[954,1058,3358,3391]" name="Mexico" pageId="8" pageNumber="627">Mexico</collectingCountry>
. Monotypic.
</subSubSection>
</paragraph>
